Did Dayanand Consider Himself Outside Hinduism?
No. Dayanand saw himself as reforming Hindu society and restoring what he believed was the original Vedic religion. Followers of the Arya Samaj generally consider themselves Hindus, although some of their beliefs differ significantly from many mainstream Hindu traditions.
The main idea behind his teachings can be summarized as:
Worship the one formless God, learn from the Vedas, use reason, perform righteous actions, and avoid practices that he believed were not supported by Vedic teachings.
